=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;"> pointed</a>=C2=A0out=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/30048191.260538/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9FcHNpbG9uV=
Ghlb3J5L3N0YXR1cy8xNjA1MzA3MjM2NDM1MzQ5NTA0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8cab12=
34" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">that</a> in fact rates have gone=C2=A0<em>down</em>, and compe=
titors=E2=80=99 stocks have gone up, since Musk closed his deal to buy Twit=
ter Inc., even as Tesla=E2=80=99s stock has plunged; Tesla is down because =
of Musk, not rates. Still it is interesting to see Musk endorsing=C2=A0Secu=
rities Analysis 101. Less than two years ago, it looked like Musk might hav=
e transcended Securities Analysis 101. If Musk=E2=80=99s businesses are val=
ued based on the expected value of their future cash flows then that=E2=80=
=99s=C2=A0<em>fine</em>, I guess, but it is a disappointment. Tesla is appa=
rently worth $440 billion based on its cash flows; it was worth $1.2 billio=
n based on the Elon Markets Hypothesis.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway Musk does seem to be pretty full time a=
t Twitter, though he has said that <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbu=
siness.com/click/30048191.260538/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2=
