t you could be spending, you know, driving your cab for money? Wouldn=E2=80=
=99t it be better if JFK had a dispatch system that let cabs go directly to=
 the terminal and pick up customers? Like, instead of waiting in the dispat=
ch lot until you are needed, you just keep driving fares around until you=
=E2=80=99re needed, and then you go right to the terminal? Like if there we=
re a system for matching supply and demand in real time, instead of keeping=
 lots of cabs idle in a parking lot?=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So two enterprising Queens men, Daniel Abayev =
and Peter Leyman,=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cwith the help of Russian hackers,=E2=80=9D =
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30048191.260538/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cuanVzdGljZS5nb3YvdXNhby1zZG55L3ByL3R3by1tZW4tYXJyZXN0ZWQtY29uc=
3BpcmluZy1ydXNzaWFuLW5hdGlvbmFscy1oYWNrLXRheGktZGlzcGF0Y2gtc3lzdGVtLWpmay1h=
aXJwb3J0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcc8bf62c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscop=
e=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> allegedly fixed the sy=
stem</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At various times between November 2019 and Nov=
ember 2020, ABAYEV and LEYMAN, working with others, successfully hacked the=
 Dispatch System. =C2=A0They used their unauthorized access to alter the Di=
spatch System and move specific taxis to the front of the line, thereby all=
owing drivers of those taxis to skip other taxi drivers waiting in the line=
. =C2=A0ABAYEV and LEYMAN charged taxi drivers $10 each time they were adva=
nced to the front of the line. =C2=A0Taxi drivers learned that they could s=
kip the taxi line by paying $10 to members of the Hacking Scheme through wo=
rd of mouth, and members of the Hacking Scheme offered some taxi drivers wa=
ivers of the $10 fee in exchange for recruiting other taxi drivers to pay t=
he $10 fee to skip the taxi line. =C2=A0The Hacking Scheme also used large =
group chat threads in order to communicate with taxi drivers. =C2=A0For exa=
mple, when the Hacking Scheme had access to the Dispatch System for the day=
, a member of the Hacking Scheme would message the group chat threads, =E2=
=80=9CShop open.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">ABAYEV and LEYMAN=E2=80=99s scheme resulted in=
 large numbers of taxi drivers skipping the taxi line. =C2=A0Over the cours=
e of the scheme, they enabled as many as 1,000 fraudulently expedited taxi =
trips a day.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CI know that the Pentagon is being hac=
ked[.]. =C2=A0So, can=E2=80=99t we hack the taxi industry[?],=E2=80=9D Abay=
ev allegedly texted one of the Russian hackers, before they actually did. L=
ike, fine, fine, you=E2=80=99re not supposed to hack the dispatch system, t=
hey were stealing the money, sure. But surely it was=C2=A0<em>worth=C2=A0</=
em>$10 to these drivers to skip a multi-hour wait for a fare?=C2=A0Arrest t=
hese guys, fine, but shouldn=E2=80=99t JFK be copying their idea?=C2=A0</p>
